data.description: This beautiful, unrestricted, property in the Texas hill country is a MUST SEE! *Motivated Sellers* This home has deep history in Kendall County, while still offering many modern day amenities. The original portion of the home was used as the original Kendall County School House, however is not recognized by the county as a historical site. The age of the home is unkown, but is thought to have been built between approximatley 1860s-1880s. The original school house has been added onto, expanding the total square footage of the home to roughly 3407sqft. This 4 bedroom 2 bath home has many amazing features that tie the history of the house, with modern luxuries. This home features a HUGE master suite, bathroom, and closet, great living and entertaining areas, the one car garage has a small workshop off the side providing a great space for all kinds of projects. An all new roof with new radiant decking, each room has a return air vent, as well as two AC units, 3 and 5 ton units, the home is well insulated and keeps temperatures very stable even with the homes age. The units are currently serviced annually. Included in the sale are all major appliances, Maytag Refrigerator, Gas Thermador Oven, Samsung Washer, and a Gas Samsung Dryer. The home sits on 3.2 acres with lots of frontage on Wasp Creek Rd, a beautiful pool and entertaining area in the backyard, huge back porch, a private well and two septic tanks, two 3,000 gallon storage tanks, storage shed, a 50 amp RV hookup, and a swingset. The cabana measures approximatley 900sqft, giving tons of room for entertaining or relaxing.    Schedule your showing today!
